<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS--><strong style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Successful things to note:</strong></p>
<ul style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Videos were very well&nbsp;received;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Video annotations with arrows and text were important;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Sorting audio/headphones on all PCs was also important (all learners were silent and focused during training);</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Keep the presentations to whole staff to a minimum &ndash; we did ten minute intro and fifteen minute plenary;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Differentiation was an absolute must &ndash; ours seemed to work well.</li>
</ul>
<div style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS--><strong style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Things to improve upon:</strong></div>
<div style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->
<ul style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Some of the resources were ordered incorrectly (d&rsquo;oh!);</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Some learners watched the video then did the activity rather than pausing. Clearer instruction required;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Some learners like badges (physical ones) and others do not;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Nearly all learners like mugs and lanyards are popular too;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->Remember to set permissions on folders so learners do not accidentally move them;</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->More time; As a school staff we would have benefitted from more time to start creating resources and discussing how Frog will be used.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->This is the first Frog INSET we will run. There is a planned dedicated session in September before it is launched with the pupils. Between now and then we will run workshops with staff wanting to achieve their aims for using the platform. But this was a big deal &ndash; first impressions count for a lot and I hope we have made a very positive impression on as many of our staff as we could. This was also my first time using Frog and it showed &ndash; a bit.</p>
