              <title>Problem-solving in cartoon universities</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/271</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/271</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[Higher order professional skills, such as critical thinking and problem solving, need either a practice environment or a rich scenario for their development, and preferably also a community of fellow professionals.

This postgraduate certificate course for university staff uses multimedia case studies of two fictional universities – ‘Crumpton’ and ‘Mullock’ – featuring realistic scenarios presented in cartoon form. Online communication tools allow learners to discuss the problems raised and recommend solutions, linking into face-to-face classes for those able to attend them.

[Alan Staley]
]]></description>
